As #global citizens, it is essential for us to address the critical situation in #France following the tragic death of young #Nahel (God rest his soul in eternal peace). The ongoing #protests and #riots in response to this incident highlight the urgency for justice, accountability, and meaningful reforms. We must advocate for transparency, thorough investigations, and systemic changes that promote social cohesion, equality, and improved relations between communities and law enforcement. It is crucial to support efforts that strive towards a fairer and more just society.

When president #Macron chooses to attend a concert during such a crisis, it is seen as disrespectful and a lack of empathy for the family of young #Nahel (God rest his soul in eternal peace). It can also be seen as a failure to prioritize the needs and concerns of the people. This can lead to public dissatisfaction and criticism, as people may feel that their leader is disconnected from the realities and challenges they are facing.

It is important for #PresidentMacron and his government to strike a balance between their personal activities and their responsibilities during times of crisis. They need to be visible, empathetic, engage with the public, and work towards resolving the issues at hand.

We must acknowledge that certain communities in #France face economic disparities and social challenges, including the existence of ghettos and the terrible conditions in which many people live. These disparities can hinder the integration process and perpetuate social divisions. It is the responsibility of the government to address these challenges and create equal opportunities for all citizens, while actively working to eliminate ghettos and improve housing conditions.

Efforts should be focused on breaking the cycle of poverty, ensuring access to quality education, creating job opportunities, and improving living conditions in marginalized areas. By addressing these socio-economic inequalities, the government can foster greater social cohesion and create an environment where every individual has a fair chance to succeed.

When such a tragic and distressing incident occurs, which leads to widespread and nationwide riots and protests, along with accusations of racism and inequality, it is vital for the #FrenchGovernment to respond comprehensively. This includes conducting thorough investigations, ensuring accountability, and implementing systemic reforms to promote social and economic justice.

Open and transparent communication from the government is crucial in addressing concerns, building trust, and demonstrating a genuine commitment to justice and fairness.

President #Macron and his government must actively engage with communities, seeking their input and participation in decision-making processes that directly affect their lives.

Leadership during times of crisis demands empathy, understanding, and a steadfast commitment to inclusivity and socio-economic progress.

As global citizens, we must advocate for these values, supporting efforts to create a society where every individual, regardless of their background, has an equal opportunity to thrive and contribute.

tweet_text:
ğŸ§ Decentralization: The Path to Ensuring Freedom of Expression on Social Media

In the current world, there are four things that no one can change: the family you are born into, the nationality you have, your ethnicity, and lastly, censorship on social media.

The Turkish elections have demonstrated that despite Elon's good intentions to make Twitter the digital agora of this era, achieving it in a centralized manner is impossible. Governments, large institutions, and media outlets will do everything possible to pressurize Twitter into censoring comments they dislike, since they have Elon to target. In order for Twitter to reach everyone, it will have to conform to the rules of each country. If a country has censorship rules, like Turkey, Twitter will have to censor content.

I don't understand why Elon is attempting something incredibly mega-bureaucratic, fighting against governments, media outlets, and others to make X the centralized source of truth. A decentralized social network that operates similar to Bitcoin would be a much less bureaucratic option and easier to scale to all countries. Additionally, in this way, individuals in positions of power would not have the means to target a specific person since we are all replaceable within a decentralized system. We are all equally important to a certain degree. In contrast, if something happens to Elon Musk and he is no longer the owner of X, what would happen to the platform? Would it maintain these principles of freedom or return to censorship? Even @jack, the creator of Twitter, thinks the same way.

Utilizing blockchain technology for message validation and transmission is the correct option in my opinion. By paying a small fee, you could express yourself freely and securely forever. Not only that, but the platform could automatically monetize itself, making likes, retweets, and follows a way to reward content creators. The simple act of paying to post tweets would practically eliminate 99% of bots, and users would think twice before tweeting or posting.

I don't believe it will be easy, but I do believe that this is the path to follow. If we want to ensure freedom of expression forever, we cannot rely solely on one person, in this case, Decentralization: The Path to Ensuring Freedom of Expression on Social Media. Instead, we should come together, just as Bitcoin functions, to create the true digital agora of the future.

Elon's work with X is highly appreciated, and it is evident that he is trying everything to make X the source of truth and freedom of expression. However, I believe that for this breakthrough to happen, it needs to be decentralized.

Thank you for reading,
Felix.

We at the ADC deeply mourn the loss of Nahel, French Algerian teenager recently murdered by French police.  This serves as a painful reminder that the scourges of anti-Arabness, Anti-Amazigh and Islamophobia aren't confined to any one nation's borders. 

We stand with the respective communities around the globe in calling for a stop to such injustices perpetrated by the French government. We firmly condemn the continued discrimination faced by Arabs, Amazigh and Muslims in France, which perpetuates harmful stereotypes, fuels hatred, and threatens the safety of our community members worldwide.

We, as Arab Americans, understand the shared struggle and empathize deeply with the victims of such bias and bigotry. We reaffirm our commitment to promoting understanding, inclusivity, and respect across ethnic and religious lines.

The French government has for far too long masqueraded their vile violence, hatred and bigotry of Arabs, Africans, Amazigh, Muslims and communities of color as â€œfreedom.â€ They must be held accountable by the global community for their long history of abuses against our collective communities. 

We call for justice for Nahel, and for all victims of racial and religious hatred and violence. #JusticeForNahel
